  "description": "A morphism is a directed connection from one [object](./object.md) to another inside a [category](./category.md). It extends a plain [directed relation](../../../../../terms/directed-graph.md) with the requirement that morphisms compose: if f goes from A to B and g goes from B to C, then there is a composite g ∘ f going from A to C, and this composition is associative.",
